Great choice!  
**Axios** fetches the **HTML source** of the web page as a string (not a live DOM).  
You do **not** need to fetch the page againjust pass the HTML string from Axios to `node-html-parser`.

**Example:**

````javascript
const axios = require('axios');
const { parse } = require('node-html-parser');

async function getDrugName(url) {
    const response = await axios.get(url);
    const root = parse(response.data); // response.data is the HTML string
    const content = root.querySelector('#content');
    if (content) {
        return content.text.trim();
    }
    return 'N/A';
}
````

**Summary:**  
- Axios gets the HTML as a string.
- Parse that string with `node-html-parser`.
- No need to fetch the page twice!

