This structure, while it works, is a bit more verbose than necessary. The explicit `return new Promise` with manual `resolve()` calls was to ensure that the promise returned by `drgVisit` *always resolves*, even if an internal error occurs (because the `catch` block also calls `resolve()`). This allows the loop in `urlTraverse` to continue to the next item.

You can achieve the same behavior more cleanly by just making `drgVisit` an `async` function and ensuring its internal `try...catch` handles errors without re-throwing them if you want the loop to continue:

