### Summary: `axios` vs. `Puppeteer`

| Redirect Type              | How it Works                                      | `axios` Behavior                                                              | `Puppeteer` Behavior                                         |
| :------------------------- | :------------------------------------------------ | :---------------------------------------------------------------------------- | :----------------------------------------------------------- |
| **HTTP 3xx Redirect**      | Server sends `302` status + `Location` header.    | Follows by default. Can be stopped with `maxRedirects: 0` to read the header. | Follows automatically. The redirect chain is visible in events. |
| **JavaScript Redirect**    | Server sends `200` status + HTML with JS code.    | **Cannot see it.** Stops at the `200` page.                                   | **Sees it.** Executes the JS and continues to the next page. |

Your discovery proves the site uses JavaScript redirects, making **Puppeteer the correct and necessary tool** to implement your clever solution.

