The refactored approach I suggested changes the flow to be more sequential:

````
// Step 1: Get the result of the initial request, no matter what it is.
let initialResponse;
try {
    // Make initial request
} catch (error) {
    initialResponse = error.response; // Store the "error" response
}

// Step 2: Now, work with the stored response. The logic is no longer nested.
if (initialResponse.status is a redirect) {
    // ...
}

// Step 3: Make the second request in its own, separate try...catch.
try {
    // Make second request
} catch (fetchError) {
    // Handle the error from the second request
}
````

